    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01135.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">431 Stevens Street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey<ptr target="loc.01135_n1"
                        /></name>
                    <date when="1880-02-21" rend="right"><choice>
                            <abbr>Feb:</abbr>
                            <expan>February</expan>
                        </choice> 21</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear friend</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Yours of 20th, with enclosure, came safely<ptr target="loc.01135_n2"/>&#8212;Best
                thanks&#8212;Yours of four days previous also, telling me of Smith<ptr
                    target="loc.01135_n3"/> and family's removal&#8212;which quite put me out
                too&#8212;Nothing very new with me, since my return&#8212;I have not written out for
                print any notes of my jaunt yet&#8212;I am well, considering&#8212;</p>

            <p>&#8212;Addington Symonds has sent me a copy of the American edition of his "Greek Poets"<ptr
                    target="loc.01135_n4"/>&#8212;Ruskin has sent to me <pb xml:id="leaf001v"
                    facs="loc.01135.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/> five sets of my books<ptr
                    target="loc.01135_n5"/>&#8212;Does Mrs Gilchrist write to you?<ptr
                    target="loc.01135_n6"/> They are well&#8212;are all in London, except Beatrice,
                who is in Switzerland&#8212;As I write (near noon Saturday) it is snowing heavily
                here&#8212;Dr Bucke, of London, Canada is writing <hi rend="underline">my
                life</hi>&#8212;I suppose he has sent you his printed circular, asking information
                &#38;c. What do you think of the project?<ptr target="loc.01135_n7"/>&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>

            <postscript>
                <p><choice>
                        <abbr>rec'd</abbr>
                        <expan>received</expan>
                    </choice> a letter from Mrs Ritter&#8212;She speaks of a musical composition of
                    her husband, to go with my "Two Veterans"&#8212;&#38; asks if I am willing it
                    should be published&#8212;I answered expressing my consent<ptr
                        target="loc.01135_n8"/></p>
            </postscript>
